  "prompt": "What's Home Depot's return/exchange policy?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Home Depot generally has a return policy that allows customers to return most items within 90 days of purchase for a full refund or exchange, provided you have the original receipt or proof of purchase. Certain exceptions may apply, particularly for special order items, freight deliveries, and specific types of tools and equipment, which may have a shorter return period.\n\nHere are some key points about their return/exchange policy:\n\n1. **Receipts**: A sales receipt is required for a full refund. If you don't have a receipt, Home Depot may offer a store credit based on the item's lowest selling price within the last 30 days.\n\n2. **Condition of Items**: Items should typically be returned in new, unused condition with the original packaging and accessories. Opened or used items may be subject to different policies.\n\n3. **Payment Method**: Refunds are generally processed through the original payment method.\n\n4. **Extended Return Periods**: Certain items, like seasonal items or major appliances, might have extended return periods.\n\n5. **Pro account returns**: If you have a Home Depot Pro account, there might be different policies or benefits regarding returns.\n\n6. **Exclusions**: Some items are non-returnable, including custom-made items or any product that has been altered or personalized.\n\nKeep in mind that specific policies may vary by location and over time, so it's always a good idea to check the Home Depot website or contact your local store for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
